Package com.im.njams.sdk.communication.fragments

Class GenericChunkAssembly<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.im.njams.sdk.communication.fragments.GenericChunkAssembly<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the raw chunked messages as used by a reader implementation, e.g., TextMessage for JMS.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    HttpSseChunkAssembly, JMSChunkAssembly, KafkaChunkAssembly
    public abstract class GenericChunkAssembly<T>
extends Object
    Collects and merges messages that are split into several chunks.
    See resolve(Object) for details.

    cwinkler

    • Constructor Detail

      • GenericChunkAssembly

        protected GenericChunkAssembly​(Function<T,​String> keyFunction,
                               Function<T,​Map<String,​String>> headersFunction,
                               Function<T,​String> dataFunction,
                               boolean httpNginxHeaders)
        Parameters:
        keyFunction - Optional. Function that provides the unique message ID for a given message chunk. I.e., all parts (chunks) that belong to the same message must have the same key. Defaults to reading the MessageHeaders.NJAMS_CHUNK_MESSAGE_KEY_HEADER header but can be overridden here, if there is better/faster way to do this.
        headersFunction - Required. Function that provides the headers map from a given message.
        dataFunction - Required. Function that provides the actual data chunk from a given message. This is the part that is actually split into chunks and re-assembled here.

    • Method Detail

      • resolve

        public RawMessage resolve​(T partialMessage)
        Creates and returns a RawMessage from the given message only if the resulting message is complete with respect to nJAMS messages. Otherwise, this method returns null and stores the given record until it has been completed with the remaining chunks.
        Parameters:
        partialMessage - A message chunk used for resolving a complete message.
        Returns:
        The message returned for a split messages contains the headers of the first chunk only.
